<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="381" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[152,1098,1343,1655]" pageId="9" pageNumber="381">
Comments. This species has a characteristic pattern (Figs 6a, c‒d) that allows even juvenile specimens to be identified to species. 
<taxonomicName box="[649,755,1539,1562]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Neon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="381" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rayi">
<emphasis box="[649,755,1539,1562]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="381">Neon rayi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a West Palaearctic distribution and is known from the Iberian Peninsula to Kazakhstan (
<bibRefCitation author="Helsdingen, P. J. van" box="[807,1001,1568,1593]" journalOrPublisher="Database European spiders and their distribution. Taxonomy. Version 2013.1." pageId="9" pageNumber="381" publicationUrl="www.faunaeur.org" refString="Helsdingen, P. J. van (2014): Araneae. In: Fauna Europaea. Database European spiders and their distribution. Taxonomy. Version 2013.1. www. faunaeur. org [accessed on 11 January 2015]" title="Araneae" type="journal article" volumeTitle="Fauna Europaea" year="2014">Helsdingen, 2014</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Mikhailov, K. G." journalOrPublisher="Arthropoda Selecta. Supplement" pageId="9" pageNumber="381" pagination="3" refString="Mikhailov, K. G. (2013): The spiders (Arachnida: Aranei) of Russia and adjacent countries: a non-annotated checklist. Arthropoda Selecta. Supplement, 3." title="The spiders (Arachnida: Aranei) of Russia and adjacent countries: a non-annotated checklist" type="book chapter" year="2013">Mikhailov, 2013</bibRefCitation>
). It was not previously known from Israel, and the record from Upper Galilee is the southernmost in the entire range.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
